  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pulmon Verde will launch sustainable farming alternatives and activities to rehabilitate and protect the local environment. Extractive activities for gold and coal by outside companies have aggravated the socioeconomic and environmental situation of Afro Colombian families in the region and contributed to climate change. The group aims to promote the establishment of protected areas and the use of ancestral and sustainable agricultural practices. Specifically, it will organize mapping activities and a rehabilitation plan for degraded areas; promote organic practices and establish a nursery for native species; purchase seeds and materials to protect areas and establish orchards to improve food security; and provide trainings on developing protective systems.</narrative>
  </description>
